textBeforeTable: Date: Sep 29, 2012 • Site: Albany, N.Y.  • Stadium: University Field  •  Attendance: 2482 Monmouth (3-2,2-1) vs. University at Albany (4-1,2-0) The Great Danes continue NEC play next Saturday when they travel to take on Bryant University at 12:00 p.m. in Smithfield, R.I. With just under a minute and a half to go in the game, Beauvais, a redshirt freshman, recorded his first career touchdown, breaking away with a 67-yard scamper to give UAlbany their last points of the day. Defensive end Dean Mercuris quickly gave the Danes possession once again, snagging the ball off the line and ran 17 yards before being brought down at midfield. Smith entered the end zone for the third time, capping the 11-play, 53-yard drive with a seven yard explosive run up the middle, doubling up the Hawks, 48-24, with 7:20 on the clock. However, mirroring the first period, UAlbany put 21 points up on the board in the final stanza, while the defense shut out the visitors. It only took one play for the Great Danes to end the drought, as Fiacchi connected a 44-yard pass to Chillis who accelerated out of the Hawks' reach.
